{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f4b28990-12d3-4a2c-97db-b0cc77c22b2e","content":"Since there's no existing repo here, I'll give you guidance on evaluation format and best practices for MCP tool-use evaluations.\n\n## Evaluation Format\n\nA common format is YAML with structured test cases:\n\n```yaml\nevaluations:\n  - name: \"search_by_category\"\n    prompt: \"Find all electronics under $50\"\n    expected_tool_calls:\n      - tool: \"search_products\"\n        arguments:\n          category: \"electronics\"\n          max_price: 50\n    expected_result_contains:\n      - \"product_id\"\n\n  - name: \"multi_step_lookup\"\n    prompt: \"What colors does the cheapest laptop come in?\"\n    expected_tool_calls:\n      - tool: \"search_products\"\n        arguments:\n          category: \"laptops\"\n          sort_by: \"price_asc\"\n      - tool: \"get_product_details\"\n    assertions:\n      - type: \"tool_called\"\n        tool: \"get_product_details\"\n      - type: \"response_contains_any\"\n        values: [\"black\", \"silver\", \"white\"]\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n**1. Test tool selection** — Can the LLM pick the right tool?\n> *\"How many reviews does product X have?\"* → should call `get_product_reviews`, not `search_products`\n\n**2. Test argument extraction** — Can it map natural language to parameters?\n> *\"Show me red shoes in size 10\"* → `{ color: \"red\", size: 10, category: \"shoes\" }`\n\n**3. Test multi-step reasoning** — Does it chain tools correctly?\n> *\"Compare the prices of the two highest-rated headphones\"* → search → get details × 2\n\n**4. Test edge cases** — Ambiguity, missing info, no results\n> *\"Find the gizmo\"* — should it guess or ask for clarification?\n\n**5. Test negative cases** — Does it avoid hallucinating tool calls?\n> *\"What's the weather?\"* — should **not** call any product tool\n\n## Key Principles\n\n- **Ground truth matters**: every eval needs a verifiable expected outcome\n- **Cover the full tool surface**: at least one eval per tool, per important parameter\n- **Mix difficulty**: simple single-tool calls + complex multi-step chains\n- **Be specific in assertions**: check tool name, key arguments, and response content\n- **Keep prompts realistic**: use the kind of language your actual users would\n\nWant me to scaffold an evaluation file for your specific product catalog tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f188631d-04d8-4aee-a3fc-015f4449e8ef","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory appears to be empty. The user is asking a general question about evaluation format for MCP server tools. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge of MCP server evaluations and skill evaluation best practices.","outputTokens":657,"requestId":"3C09:1C1C65:1E9E356:2280601:69E81C4E"},"id":"3c373f8c-0503-4c33-8617-986c80254f84","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:54:55.357Z","parentId":"273f9a3b-a70c-48e0-9083-8f67b502d7f2"}
